formula: Expansion of eta(q^4)^10/(eta(q)^2 *eta(q^2)^3 *eta(q^8)^3* eta(q^16)^2)) - 2 in powers of q. - _G. C. Greubel_, May 28 2018
Expansion of -2 + (1/q) * chi(q)^2 * chi(q^2)^7 * chi(q^4)^2 in powers of q where chi() is a Ramanujan theta function. - _Michael Somos_, Feb 09 2019
